93
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,890
But remember, you are mine.

94
00:06:37,590 --> 00:06:38,950
Are you asking about Mr. Wu?

95
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:42,900
I don't know his background either.

96
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:45,810
But he's a good person.

97
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:49,150
In what way is he good?

98
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,659
When I'm with him,

99
00:06:54,659 --> 00:06:56,970
I don't feel like I'm serving someone.

100
00:06:59,180 --> 00:07:01,740
Instead, he treats me like a friend.

101
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,770
But it seems like he has something troubling him.

102
00:07:13,330 --> 00:07:15,210
He's always drinking alone, brooding.

103
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,900
Then do you know

104
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,000
what he does for a living?

105
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,920
It seems to have something to do with a newspaper office.

106
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,100
Sir.

107
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:43,320
One bag of candied chestnuts, please.

108
00:07:43,659 --> 00:07:44,460
Sure thing.

109
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:46,740
Here you go.

110
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,159
Would you like some candied chestnuts?

111
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:58,790
What are you doing?

112
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,590
You've twisted my arm!

113
00:08:00,790 --> 00:08:03,400
Don't try to scam me. I barely touched you.

114
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,610
Lieutenant Peng.

115
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:07,110
Don't you know your own strength?

116
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,360
Who told you to be so sneaky?

117
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:16,220
Let's go.

118
00:08:18,450 --> 00:08:19,390
What do you want to do?

119
00:08:20,030 --> 00:08:21,290
Take me to the hospital.

120
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:22,670
Let's go.

121
00:08:23,150 --> 00:08:24,020
Go by yourself.

122
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:26,580
Fine.

123
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:30,500
Lieutenant Peng, who works for the Young Marshal, is beating people!

124
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,360
Shut up.

125
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:39,510
If you don't help me, I'll fall.

126
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:43,820
Alright, I can take you to the hospital.

127
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,230
But first, tell me,

128
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,170
what were you doing at the newspaper office?

129
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:52,830
If you want to know, take me to the hospital first.

130
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:05,520
The key is in my right pocket. I can't reach it.

131
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:11,890
Take it easy.

132
00:09:12,930 --> 00:09:14,710
I can take this opportunity to search his house.

133
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,600
It's a blessing in disguise.

134
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:34,530
Lieutenant Peng, I'm just injured,

135
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,210
not dead.

136
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,320
How can you

137
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:39,610
search the house right under the owner's nose?

138
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:40,840
It's not right.

139
00:09:41,090 --> 00:09:43,080
You brought me in. It'd be a waste not to search.

140
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:56,860
What is this?

141
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,150
Being locked means...

142
00:10:07,810 --> 00:10:09,540
Such an exquisite box.

143
00:10:11,180 --> 00:10:12,900
Shouldn't it contain valuable items?

144
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:15,250
You only put half a brick in it.

145
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:20,020
This means that half brick is very important.

146
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:26,860
[Maybe she's lucky]

147
00:10:32,580 --> 00:10:33,250
What is this?

148
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,540
Can't you read?

149
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:41,410
Didn't you ask me what I do at the newspaper office?

150
00:10:42,150 --> 00:10:43,510
Actually, I'm a writer.

151
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:46,160
I write serialized novels for magazines.

152
00:10:47,630 --> 00:10:50,180
If you don't believe me, you can go ask at the newspaper office.

153
00:10:50,510 --> 00:10:53,660
The one who writes under the pen name "Moon Fairy" is none other than myself.

154
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,950
You write under a woman's name?

155
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:57,780
What kind of stuff do you write?

156
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:02,220
"The sound of heavy breathing getting closer and closer.

157
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:06,480
A pair of large hands slipped into my qipao."

158
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:08,440
What... what is this?

159
00:11:08,470 --> 00:11:09,470
Don't throw it away!

160
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:10,500
This... this...

161
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:13,260
This is my livelihood!

162
00:11:13,610 --> 00:11:15,300
You're a grown man, why can't you write something else?

163
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,520
Yet, you write erotic novels.

164
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,720
To each their own.

165
00:11:20,710 --> 00:11:21,930
But now we have a problem.

166
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,970
You've sprained my right hand.

167
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,240
I can't write.

168
00:11:26,590 --> 00:11:28,810
If I can't write the next installment of the series,

169
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:31,300
how am I supposed to make a living?

170
00:11:31,970 --> 00:11:34,750
Perfect. Take this opportunity to change your profession.

171
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,930
But I still need to submit the next installment.

172
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:39,470
I...

173
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:40,260
I'll pay

174
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,850
to hire a ghostwriter for you.

175
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:43,910
Why spend that money?

176
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:46,540
When you have free time,

177
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,470
you could come and take dictation for me, couldn't you?

178
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:50,980
I don't have time.

179
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,750
No time, huh?

180
00:11:54,170 --> 00:11:55,210
Then how about this?

181
00:11:55,730 --> 00:11:59,190
In my story, there's a womanizer who hasn't been named yet.

182
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:02,800
Why don't we call him Peng Wu?

183
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:06,840
Peng Wu sneaks into the young lady's chamber under the cover of night.

184
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,890
A lecherous grin spread across his face.

185
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:09,430
A pair of large hands...

186
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:10,440
Shut up.

187
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:13,920
If I could further pry into his life,

188
00:12:14,450 --> 00:12:16,490
I should be able to uncover his true identity.

189
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:18,620
Let me think about it.

190
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:30,730
Young Marshal.

191
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,720
Qiuting, have a seat.

192
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:35,800
Mom.

193
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:41,600
Miss Duan, do you have any business at my home?

194
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:43,030
Listen to yourself.

195
00:12:43,050 --> 00:12:44,350
Jinyao missed you.

196
00:12:44,370 --> 00:12:45,790
Is it not okay for her to come and see you?

197
00:12:46,190 --> 00:12:49,310
Qiuting, this is Dr. Frank.

198
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,620
Dr. Frank

199
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:55,540
is Germany's most renowned railway expert.

200
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:58,710
This time, thanks to Miss Jinyao,

201
00:12:58,740 --> 00:13:02,170
we were able to invite this great master.

202
00:13:02,420 --> 00:13:03,500
Dr. Frank

203
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,160
and the principal of August Middle School

204
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:06,110
